'''Maria Johanna (Marjan) Oudema''' (born 1958) is president of [[Utrecht University]]. She is also a director of Norwegian oil and gas company Statoil<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arctic.ru/international/20161019/470389.html |title=Russia and Norway to sign an agreement on seismic data collection in the Barents Sea and the Arctic Ocean / Arctic |website=Arctic.ru |date=2016-10-19 |accessdate=2016-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Ida Aamodt-Hansen |url=http://e24.no/jobb/blir-styremedlem-i-statoil/23227182 |title=Blir styremedlem i Statoil - Jobb - E24 |website=E24.no |date= |accessdate=2016-12-22}}</ref> as well as [[Het Concertgebouw]], the [[Rijksmuseum]], [[Solvay SA]] and [[SHV Holdings]]. She was previously a member of the executive committee of [[Akzo Nobel]] and executive director Strip Products Division at [[Corus Group]], now Tata Steel Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.statoil.com/en/About/CorporateGovernance/GoverningBodies/Board/Pages/MarjanOudeman.aspx |title=Maria Johanna (Marjan) Oudeman |website=Statoil.com |date= |accessdate=2016-12-22}}</ref>
